					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Steven W. Thrasher</h4>
												<p>Steven W. Thrasher, PhD, CPT, a journalist, social epidemiologist, and cultural critic, holds the Daniel Renberg chair at the Medill School of Journalism, and is on the faculty of Northwestern University’s Institute of Sexual and Gender Minority Health and Wellbeing. A former writer for the <i>Village Voice, Scientific American</i> and the <i>Guardian</i>, Thrasher is the author of the critically acclaimed book <a href="https://bookshop.org/p/books/the-viral-underclass-the-human-toll-when-inequality-and-disease-collide-steven-w-thrasher/17086534" class="external" target="_blank"><i>The Viral Underclass: The Human Toll When Inequality and Disease Collide. [Photo by C.S. Muncy]</p>
